The paper is about fraud detection in electronic commerce, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to analyze massive amounts of streaming data, which is related to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Big Data tools such as Kafka, Spark, and Cassandra, which are related to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the experimental results on a massive dataset, which is related to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
